CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 12 reads: "Teen-Queen Contestants - These fourteen young misses of the Hill District are vying for the title Teen-Queen in the annual contest sponsored by Hill City. They are, left to right:...Clara Turner"
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Clara Turner wearing light colored shirt with dark turtleneck collar, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen Contest
